snippet.textDisplay:
Hey, I have a theory for you

Guys what if the characters of PJ masks are acting that way because of neglect and abuse? My theory comes from the PJ Masks episode 12 (first half) from season 1. Luna Girl, the main villain of that episode has nobody to spend Christmas with, these children are so young and just out and night with nobody on such a beloved day, why are they out? Luna Girl says “I have nobody to spend Christmas with” in one part of the episode and that’s what gives the PJ Mask group the idea to spend it with her, also where are Owlette, Catboy, AND Gecko’s parents?! If those kids got hurt nobody would know, where are the parents in this show? We see teachers which are adults in the show so there are adults where they live.
Why was Luna Girl left out during Christmas? Either my suspicions are because she was being neglected by her family, they got drunk and forgot about her (but Disney don say nothing) OR Luna Girl could be an orphan. Another reason of this is that nobody, NOBODY AT ALL sees what happens except these kids, wouldn’t there be some adults? Everything in this show is realistic other than the magic powers and stuff so there SHOULD be cops. With all the destruction those kids do sometimes (and with all the businesses they could put in debt, referring to the episode where one of the villains stole all the toys) they would be in juvenile for a WHILE, or fined. We know the PJ masks have a home because during their transformations each episode they are seen in their room. Anyways so what do you think? Please though- give me feedback
